My persuasive writing is based on whether Gays/Lesbians should be allowed to adopt kids. When i moved to CA from GA, i found my sexual identity and i couldnt see myself being with a man, so i started to date women. Around the time i started to explore whom i was, there was a weird debate regarding whether or not it is detrimental to kids having same sex parents and it was 2010 so same sex marriage wasnt even legal yet. 

I feel like its detrimental for ANY kid when parents are involved. No matter the type of religion or sexuality the person is.. if they are horrible parents, the kids dont have a fighting chance. I honestly think that kids with the same sex parents are happier. Reason being, we dont have sex and create babies by accident. We plan and plan when to have kids. This is in no way shade to heterosexual indiviuals that have families but same sex parents make really good parents. I know there are alot of hetero couples that plan on having kids and they deserve a beautiful family but same sex couples deserve to be able to experience the same

In saying this, i think we all deserve a chance at having a family! Even if thats adopting, invitro or what have you. What matters is the happiness of the child. Now that it is
